dpul.title: Next/Previous functionality in browse or search categories not advancing as expected

comments.body:
Yeah I think this is a side effect of grouping DPUL does.

Can we just get rid of this? Next/previous is really buggy in general for Blacklight, especially with things like multiple tabs.
What would we have in lieu of it?
I usually just use the browser back button and go to the next thing, or use browser tabs

Ellen and I have reviewed the previous/next issues. and have found different functionality depending on how you navigate to different groupings of the collection.
BROWSE: in browse category, you have no next/previous option from the list, but when you select the item you do have the next/previous option--which doesn't work at all well. 
Mirroring this.....

FACETS from home page (by provenance, for example): you have the option to use next/previous in list search display, that seems to function appropriately (when something other than "relevance" is selected for sorting). But when you select an item from the list search display, the option for previous/next disappears.  

If we had a choice, the browse categories would mirror the facets search, in terms of the previous/next buttons.
This would be seen as the best option available right now, but something we would like to revisit when the 3.0 upgrade happens. 
Are you intending to just remove the item level previous/next, @tpendragon and @hackartisan ?
